alert.note: Alert for Western Aleutians (Alaska) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 28 at 4:08PM AKST until January 29 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM AKST SUNDAY... * WHAT...Winds 50 to 70 mph with gusts up to 80 mph expected. * WHERE...Western Aleutians. * WHEN...From noon today to 6 AM AKST Sunday. * IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris and damage property. Travel could be difficult. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong southeasterly winds are developing across the Western Aleutians this afternoon with gusts over 70 mph already observed in Shemya. Winds will continue to increase through the evening hours before temporarily subsiding as southeasterly winds shift to southwesterly with the passage of the upper low. After a brief break in winds, southwesterly gusts to as high as 75 mph are expected to develop after midnight, gradually tapering off through the early morning hours on Sunday.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind.
